flowRoot.flowPara: KB is private to Thinker. Thinker also has access to Actor's actions and can override them (similar to the ego and superego overriding the id, in Freudian terms). The Actor can program the Thinker, but I've argued that this would not be very significant during the bootstrap stage.
KB is shared with Actor. So Actor can directly create thoughts independent of Thinker.
(But it raises some questions... see email)
Thinker is built on top of Actor, using a primitive language or what may be called a "pre-logic".
In this case Thinker may be modified by Actor in a number of ways, but I'm not sure if this is really beneficial / feasible / easy to implement.
